  "project": {
    "description": [
      "Primary source is the uploaded PDF titled Occupational Health and Worker Engagement. It is a narrative academic review based on a transcript about why workers do not engage with occupational health services. It argues that non-engagement is not simple worker ignorance but a multi-level response to unequal access, weak visibility, preventive-surveillance ambiguity, confidentiality concerns, stigma, occupational damage, presenteeism, managerial gatekeeping, GP-first help-seeking, sectoral pressures, and a dominant evidence base that privileges cost-effectiveness over worker experience. The mapping below treats the document as a Goguen-style institution for OHWork strategic foresight, with governance and operational-delivery focus areas. Core source anchors include the review's central thesis and framing , its account of unequal access and opaque provision , its analysis of prevention, trust, confidentiality, stigma, disclosure, presenteeism, managers, GP pathways, NHS context, evidence-base critique, research contentions, implications, and conclusion         .",
      "The institution currently includes 12 signatures, 122 sentences, 9 models, and 201 satisfaction relations, with 0 web-grounded contextual findings."
    ],
    "name": "OHWork_Worker_Centred_Occupational_Health_Engagement_Institution",
    "promptTemplate": {
      "defaultAssumptions": "[No additional refinements provided. State reasonable assumptions.]",
      "instructions": "Add project refinements and click Generate AI Prompt to produce a prompt for interpreting the current institution settings, tensions, and likely implementation consequences.",
      "promptText": [
        "You are an expert in institutions, implementation, systems governance, and scenario analysis.",
        "Write a short report (700\u20131,000 words) interpreting the likely outcomes of the current institution under the selected parameter settings.",
        "",
        "Institution summary:",
        "- Institution name: OHWork_Worker_Centred_Occupational_Health_Engagement_Institution",
        "- Organisation: OHWork",
        "- Analysis mode: Strategic foresight",
        "- Source documents: helenoneil.pdf",
        "- Signatures: 12; Sentences: 122; Models: 9; Satisfaction relations: 201",
        "",
        "Current parameter settings (0\u2013100 unless marked otherwise):",
        "{{PARAMETERS_LIST}}",
        "",
        "Please do ALL of the following:",
        "1) Explain how these settings shape institutional coherence, implementability, and likely adaptation pressure.",
        "2) Discuss expected effects on governance, stakeholder alignment, compliance, and operational stability.",
        "3) Identify the most important failure modes, translation gaps, and weak satisfaction relations.",
        "4) Recommend 5 practical next actions for strengthening the institution and its implementation.",
        "5) Be explicit about uncertainty, assumptions, and what additional evidence would reduce ambiguity.",
        "",
        "Project refinements supplied by the user:",
        "{{REFINEMENTS}}"
      ],
      "title": "AI Prompt Generator"
    }
  },
